      • implementJar

        public void implementJar​(Class<?> token,
                         Path jarFile)
                  throws info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException
        Produces .jar file implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

        Generated class full name should be same as full name of the type token with Impl suffix added.

        During implementation creates temporary folder to store temporary .java and .class files.

        Specified by:
        implementJar in interface info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.JarImpler
        Throws:
        info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException - if the given class cannot be generated for one of such reasons:
        • Some arguments are null
        • Error occurs during implementation via implement(Class, Path)
        • The process is not allowed to create files or directories.
        • JavaCompiler failed to compile implemented class
        • The problems with I/O occurred during implementation.

      • main

        public static void main​(String[] args)
                 throws info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException
        This function is used to choose which way of implementation to execute. Runs Implementor in two possible ways:
        • 2 arguments: className rootPath - runs implement(Class, Path) with given arguments
        • 3 arguments: -jar className jarPath - runs implementJar(Class, Path) with two second arguments
        If arguments are incorrect or an error occurs during implementation returns message with information about error
        Parameters:
        args - arguments for running an application
        Throws:
        info.kgeorgiy.java.advanced.implementor.ImplerException - if arguments are invalid
